I need to fix a Django form bug where ModelChoiceField with non-PK foreign keys (using to_field parameter) shows the wrong selected option in dropdown widgets.

The issue is in /workspace/django/forms/models.py in the ModelChoiceField class. The prepare_value() method needs to be fixed to handle cases where to_field_name is set but the value passed is a pk (not a model instance).

Current code (line 1572-1578):
```python
def prepare_value(self, value):
    if hasattr(value, "_meta"):
        if self.to_field_name:
            return value.serializable_value(self.to_field_name)
        else:
            return value.pk
    return super().prepare_value(value)
```

The fix needed: When to_field_name is set and value is not a model instance (just a pk), we need to look up the object by pk and extract the to_field value.

